{
  "version": 1,
  "name": "Inductor Kickback Demo",
  "lesson": {
    "title": "Inductor Kickback Demo",
    "description": "Press and hold the tact button: USB → 470Ω → inductor → red LED → ground. Current builds in the coil and the LED glows. Release the button — the magnetic field collapses and the inductor “kicks back,” driving a short bright flash through the LED (the coil resists a sudden drop in current). Compare lesson 8 (no inductor — LED snaps off) and lesson 28 (capacitor pulse when the switch changes). LED at 90° (anode north)."
  },
